WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.280
[Amit Varma]: How often do you look around yourself and think, this was not supposed to happen? If

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:14.920
[Amit Varma]: you live in India, there is actually much reason to do just that. We were not supposed

00:00:14.920 --> 00:00:19.920
[Amit Varma]: to be here. India was not supposed to be the vibrant, diverse democracy that it is today.

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:25.680
[Amit Varma]: Indeed, one of the core rationalizations of colonialism was, these people cannot govern

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:31.800
[Amit Varma]: themselves. And yet, here we are, a functioning democracy for over 70 years. And a big part

00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:36.720
[Amit Varma]: of this is our constitution, which not only shaped our systems of governance and the rules

00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:42.160
[Amit Varma]: of the game, but also shaped how all of us think about our country and our own role in

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:46.600
[Amit Varma]: it. Now, there is much that I find wrong with our constitution. It does not go far enough

00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:51.600
[Amit Varma]: to protect individual rights. It is way too long and that dilutes its utility, yada, yada,

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:56.640
[Amit Varma]: yada. It is also true that our constitution takes many elements from other constitutions

00:00:56.640 --> 00:01:01.280
[Amit Varma]: and that a chunk of it is a reproduction of the Government of India Act of 1935. It is

00:01:01.280 --> 00:01:06.280
[Amit Varma]: also true that some of the values it pays homage to could be called enlightenment values

00:01:06.280 --> 00:01:11.640
[Amit Varma]: and many of the founders were influenced by great thinkers of the West. But it is not,

00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:17.040
[Amit Varma]: as many have alleged in the past, a copy-paste job. The impetus behind it, what the author

00:01:17.040 --> 00:01:22.720
[Amit Varma]: Madhav Khosla calls, quote, the cultivation of democratic citizenship, stop quote, was

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:28.280
[Amit Varma]: unique to our circumstances and no aspect of our constitution was blindly copied from

00:01:28.280 --> 00:01:33.560
[Amit Varma]: elsewhere. There was much debate, much thought given to every element of our constitution,

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:39.200
[Amit Varma]: not just the what, but also the why. And these debates are fascinating for anyone who wants

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:44.320
[Amit Varma]: to understand not just this imperfect and mutating document that is our guiding light,

00:01:44.320 --> 00:01:50.000
[Amit Varma]: but also why it is the way it is and why we are the way we are.

